The UN's condemnation comes after the country's security apparatus opened fire on pro-democracy protestors camped outside the army headquarters, reportedly killed at least 13 people.  

The Military and the umbrella body representing the protestors had been negotiating for weeks over who should lead the country in a civilian-led Transitional Authority following the ouster of former President, Omar al Bashir, in April. Sherwin Bryce-Pease reports... --SABC--